Business Brief -- Shaw Cablesystems Ltd.:
   Canadian Firm to Acquire
   Closely Held CL Systems
The acquisition of closely held CL Systems will add
320,000 cable subscribers to Shaw's existing
550,000-subscriber base, ranking it behind Rogers
Communications Inc. and Le Groupe Videotron Ltee., Mr. Shaw
said. He said it will boost Shaw Cablesystems' annual revenue
to about C$235 million from C$165 million currently.
   Mr. Shaw said the company will draw on existing bank lines
of credit to finance the purchase.
   Noel Bambrough, president and chief executive officer of
CL Systems, said the company's majority owner, David Graham,
decided to sell the concern for "personal reasons." He didn't
elaborate.
   CL Systems and Shaw Cablesystems are based in Toronto.